<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Chart on Saitech</title><link>https://saitech.blog/tags/chart/</link><description>Recent content in Chart on Saitech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 06 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://saitech.blog/tags/chart/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>SkyChart on Arch Linux</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/skychart-on-arch-linux/</link><pubDate>Sun, 06 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/skychart-on-arch-linux/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/skychart-on-arch-linux/1.png" alt="Featured image of post SkyChart on Arch Linux" />&lt;p>If you&amp;rsquo;re into stargazing or just like pretty sky maps, &lt;strong>SkyChart (Cartes du Ciel)&lt;/strong> is a solid planetarium software. Works great on Linux, and yes, you can run it on Arch btw.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="install-skychart">Install SkyChart
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>You can install it straight from the official Arch repos:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo yay -S skychart
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>This will pull in everything you need to get started.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="running-it">Running It
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Once installed, just launch it with:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">skychart
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>The interface is a bit old-school, but it’s powerful. You can load catalogs, plot celestial events, and even connect to telescopes.&lt;/p>
